{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782643279096,"sessionID":"ses_0f234de66ffeoXYFpTxjPoAdc8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_wyhBccjiO9k3sSbwJFrD50bh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"include":"platform-capability-check.json","path":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs","pattern":"\"capabilityId\": \"file-access-and-saf\"|\"status\":|\"decision\":|\"targetCapabilitySearch\":|\"targetApiOrLibrary\":|\"targetStrategy\":|\"notes\":"},"output":"Found 31 matches\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\platform-capability-check.json:\n  Line 648:       \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\r\n\n  Line 650:       \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\r\n\n  Line 658:       \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie MediaLibraryKit / ohos.file.photo_access_helper (getPhotoAccessHelper, PhotoAccessHelper.getAlbums, album/media asset APIs) exists in the current SDK, but phase-04 home/history source behavior only consumes bundled drawable resources and does not browse user albums.\",\r\n\n  Line 659:       \"targetStrategy\": \"Treat the phase-04 media-library requirement as a source-analysis false positive. Implement home/history images from packaged app media resources only; do not add album discovery, gallery picker, or media permission scaffolding in this phase unless later source-backed behavior proves a real user-media flow.\",\r\n\n  Line 691:       \"notes\": \"Phase-04 implementation preserved bundled-resource media rendering for the scoped home/history surfaces and did not widen the phase into album discovery or picker flows.\",\r\n\n  Line 745:       \"capabilityId\": \"file-access-and-saf\",\r\n\n  Line 2410:       \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\r\n\n  Line 2412:       \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\r\n\n  Line 2417:       \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit Want/URI APIs (`ohos.app.ability.want.Want`, `ohos.app.ability.want_constant.Flags`) exist for real cross-app URI/file sharing, but phase-05 detail/cart source behavior does not invoke them.\",\r\n\n  Line 2418:       \"targetStrategy\": \"Treat the phase-05 file/document/share capability as not applicable for detail/cart. Keep the phase focused on detail/cart state and packaged-resource rendering; if a later source-backed share flow is implemented, route it through HarmonyOS Want-based sharing with explicit URI permission flags instead of introducing Android SAF assumptions.\",\r\n\n  Line 2438:       \"notes\": \"Phase-05 detail/cart source behavior does not include any implemented file access, document picker, or URI sharing workflow. The share affordance is present only as an empty button handler, so closing this capability as not-applicable preserves actual source behavior instead of inventing SAF scope.\",\r\n\n  Line 3100:       \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\r\n\n  Line 3102:       \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\r\n\n  Line 3107:       \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie ArkUI `Image` and ImageKit `ohos.multimedia.image.createImageSource(String)` exist for real image display/processing, but phase-05 detail/cart source behavior only needs static packaged-image rendering.\",\r\n\n  Line 3108:       \"targetStrategy\": \"Resolve the capability as not applicable for phase-05. Implement the detail/cart visuals with normal HarmonyOS Image rendering from packaged media; do not add zoom, reset, metadata, or EXIF UI unless a later source-backed requirement proves a real image viewer flow.\",\r\n\n  Line 3129:       \"notes\": \"The current phase only shows packaged images inside detail and cart cards. There is no source-backed zoom, pan, reset, metadata, or EXIF flow to preserve, so adding a gesture viewer here would over-implement beyond the source app.\",\r\n\n  Line 3913:       \"status\": \"verified-direct\",\r\n\n  Line 3915:       \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\r\n\n  Line 3920:       \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie LocalizationKit resource model (`ohos.base.ResourceStr`, `ohos.resource.AppResource`, `ohos.resource_manager.ResourceManager`) with standard HarmonyOS `string.json`/`color.json` resources\",\r\n\n  Line 3921:       \"targetStrategy\": \"Phase 01 migrates Android labels, start-window colors, and resource-backed UI text into HarmonyOS descriptor/resource files, with AppResource helpers for Cangjie access where needed. Batch 3 also removes hard-coded route-shell labels by routing them through `foodike_resources.cj` and `app_router.cj` before display in `bootstrap_page.cj`.\",\r\n\n  Line 3960:       \"notes\": \"Batch 1 confirmed the active entry/module descriptors and resource files compile together. Batch 3 moved phase-01 route-shell labels off hard-coded English text and added a focused route/theme contract test, but `cjpm test` remains harness-blocked because `entry/cjpm.toml` lacks declared dependencies for imported `kit.AbilityKit`, `kit.ArkUI`, and `ohos.resource` packages.\",\r\n\n  Line 5770:       \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\r\n\n  Line 5772:       \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\r\n\n  Line 5777:       \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit permission APIs exist (`ohos.ability_access_ctrl.AtManager`, `ohos.security.permission_request_result.PermissionRequestResult`) but are not required by phase-02 startup/session/navigation source behavior.\",\r\n\n  Line 5778:       \"targetStrategy\": \"Treat the phase-02 permission requirement as a source-analysis false positive. Do not add permission prompts or protected-access scaffolding during startup/session/navigation implementation unless later source-backed phases introduce real protected APIs.\",\r\n\n  Line 5801:       \"notes\": \"Phase-02 source review confirms runtime permissions are not required by the startup/session/navigation batch. The accepted phase-02 test build report is PASS, so this row no longer relies on stale blocked-test notes.\",\r\n\n  Line 6097:       \"status\": \"platform-replaced\",\r\n\n  Line 6099:       \"targetCapabilitySearch\": [\r\n\n  Line 6104:       \"targetApiOrLibrary\": \"HarmonyOS Cangjie AbilityKit app-entry APIs (`ohos.app.ability.ui_ability.UIAbility`, `UIAbilityContext`, `Want`) plus ArkUI `Navigation`/`NavPathStack` or `Router` for in-app startup and route flow\",\r\n\n  Line 6105:       \"targetStrategy\": \"Resolve the source Android platform component surface as a HarmonyOS platform replacement: model app startup in the target `UIAbility`/descriptor entry, keep splash-like gating inside bootstrap state before rendering the main route, and implement onboarding/home navigation using the existing ArkUI route shell instead of Android `Application`, `ComponentActivity`, and `core-splashscreen` APIs.\",\r\n\n  Line 6135:       \"notes\": \"Phase-02 only needs app entry and startup lifecycle gating. The platform replacement is carried by precise entry/startup endpoints, and the accepted phase-02 test build report now backs the startup-store contract evidence.\",\r\n","metadata":{"matches":31,"truncated":false},"title":"\"capabilityId\": \"file-access-and-saf\"|\"status\":|\"decision\":|\"targetCapabilitySearch\":|\"targetApiOrLibrary\":|\"targetStrategy\":|\"notes\":","time":{"start":1782643279050,"end":1782643279093}},"id":"prt_f0dd1bfcc0013eRsJLd6tingIh","sessionID":"ses_0f234de66ffeoXYFpTxjPoAdc8","messageID":"msg_f0dd14468001iEMrHkB8VRLRim"}}
